---
description: 
globs: services/graphql-engine/migrations/**
alwaysApply: false
---
When creating database migrations, we should start by creating a migration with hasura.

This should be run as a script:

The `[migration-name]` should be replaced with a snake_case name for the migration (omitting the square braces).

the --up-sql and --down-sql flags should contain the specific migration code.

```
scripts/run-hasura migrate create [migration-name] \
      --up-sql "ALTER TABLE ..." \
      --down-sql "ALTER TABLE ..."
```

The output of that command includes a migration timestamp id, which can be used to find the file in
services/graphql-engine-migrations directory to find the up and down sql files should the require further editing.

The migration can be executed by running:

```
scripts/run-hasura metadata apply
scripts/run-hasura migrate apply
scripts/run-hasura metadata apply
```